window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Gen Beaufont might be from fifteenth century London, but modern day Los Angeles is her home.</b></p> <p>And corrupt politicians are trying to destroy her city. Somethings never change, no matter how many centuries tick by.</p> <p><b>When Gen learns that the political leaders of LA are using their powers for evil, she springs into action.</b></p> <p>She might work with criminals, but only to protect the greater good. These politicians are harming the people all for their own selfish gains.</p> <p><b>And sadly, the one person who could help Gen to stop this is a traitor and wants her dead. Gen has her work cut out for her, stopping insider trading, unethical business kick backs and bringing down the mastermind behind all the exploitations in Los Angeles.</b></p> <p>Oh, and also, she needs to catch up on a hundred years of music and television so that she can finally get all the pop culture references that keep flying over her head.</p> <p><b>Can Gen Beaufont expose the mastermind behind the corruption and save Los Angeles from the brink of chaos?</b> Or will the criminals lurking in the shadows take over, unleashing an evil so rampant that it could consume not just the city, but the entire world?</p>"; 
